public class MoleculeIterators.MoleculeAtomIterator
extends java.lang.Object
implements MoleculeIterators.AtomIteratorInterface

Enumerates atoms of a Molecule. Beyond functionalities required by the implemented interface the choice of inclusion/ exclusion of hydrogen atoms is provided.

setIncludeH

public void setIncludeH(boolean includeH)
Sets how hydrogen atoms are handled by the enumerator. Hydrogen atoms are listed by default this if they are not needed this method should be called with an argument false.

Parameters:
includeH - indicates if hydrogen atoms are enumerated or not
